{"cursor":"8054","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Muslim scholar\n| notability = Muslim scholar era = Islamic golden age style=\"color:#cef2e0;\"\n| image = caption = name = 'Abu al-Hasan Ali ibn IsmaÊ»el al-AshÊ»ari' title= 'al-\n| Ash'ari' birth_date = death_date = Maddhab = Sunni school_tradition|= Sunni\n| ethnicity = region = main_interests = Islamic theology notable_ideas= works =\n| MaqÄlÄt al-eslÄmÄ«yÄ«n, ed. H.\n| Ritter, Istanbul, 1929-30 KetÄb al-loma, ed. and\n| tr. R.C. McCarthy, Beirut, 1953 KetÄb al-ebÄna'an osÅ«l al-dÄ«Äna tr. W.C. Klein, New Haven, 1940\n| influences = al-Jubba'i, Imam Shafi'i influenced = |\n}}\n\n'AbÅ« al-Hasan AlÄ« ibn IsmÄ'Ä«l al-Ash'arÄ«' (874 â 936) () was a Muslim Arab\ntheologian and an early follower of the Mu'tazila school {{cite book\n | last = Ibn Asaakir first = title = \"Tabyeen\" (p.131) quoting from al-Ash'ari\n | publisher = year = page = quote = We wrote a large work regarding the\n | attributes which we called 'Kitab ul-Jawabaat Fi as-Sifat 'an Masa'il Ahl iz-\n | Zaigh wa ash-Shubuhat', in which we criticized a (previous) book of ours\n | which we had written a long time ago in which there was a validation of the\n | madhhab of the Mu'tazilah - there not being a book being authored for them\n | like it! Then Allah, the Sublime, made the truth clear to us, and so we\n | turned back from that (I'tizal) and we criticized it and made its misguidance\n | clear. isbn = }}\n before studying under Abdullah ibn Sa'eed ibn Kullaab whom he was a\nfollower of according to Ibn Taymiyyah. During this period of his life, a number\nof al-Ash'ari's students went on to propagate this sunni theology.\n","linknr":269,"url":"Abu_al-Hasan_al-Ash'ari","recorded":1374783770,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Abu_al-Hasan_al-Ash%27ari&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Abu_al-Hasan_al-Ash%27ari&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?ac